The paper discusses kernel principal component analysis (KPCA) and its use in semisupervised learning, which are topics related to machine learning and computer vision. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions a new convex optimization problem, which falls under the category of numerical analysis, making cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) a likely sub-category as well. Finally, the paper proposes a new model for semisupervised learning, which can be considered a form of optimization, making cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) a possible sub-category.
